docs.abstract: Kyle Lewis of the Seattle Mariners is a top contender for the American League Rookie of the Year Award in a shortened season upended by postponements and delays.
docs.snippet: Kyle Lewis of the Seattle Mariners is a top contender for the American League Rookie of the Year Award in a shortened season upended by postponements and delays.
docs.lead_paragraph: Along with the rest of the world, athletes have had their careers upended by the coronavirus pandemic. They are giving The New York Times an intimate look at their journeys in periodic installments through the rest of the year. Read Lewis’s first two installments here and here.

docs.abstract: Wilson, the Aces’ All-Star forward, isn’t the only one from Las Vegas deserving of honors this year.
docs.snippet: Wilson, the Aces’ All-Star forward, isn’t the only one from Las Vegas deserving of honors this year.
docs.lead_paragraph: Talent in the W.N.B.A. runs so deep that many teams have bench players who would start on other teams. With some of the league’s most familiar faces sitting out or having received medical exemptions for this season because of the coronavirus pandemic, under-the-radar players have seized their increased minutes as opportunities to shine. And while lesser-known players were compiling breakout seasons, some established stars were helping their teams win in unexpected ways.

headline.main: A’ja Wilson for M.V.P., and More W.N.B.A. Awards Picks

docs.abstract: Boris Johnson came into office aiming to defund the BBC and let in rivals. The coronavirus has delayed that, but the broadcaster again finds itself a punching bag for Conservatives.
docs.snippet: Boris Johnson came into office aiming to defund the BBC and let in rivals. The coronavirus has delayed that, but the broadcaster again finds itself a punching bag for Conservatives.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — It had all the ingredients for a juicy skirmish in Britain’s simmering culture war, so when the BBC announced last week that it would strip the lyrics from two popular patriotic songs in its telecast of a beloved annual concert, Conservative leaders predictably lined up to express their outrage.

headline.main: BBC Lost a Battle Over British Songs, and the War Is Far From Over
headline.print_headline: The BBC Loses a Battle Over Patriotic Songs, And the War Isn’t Over
